# Code in English

All **source code** in this project must be written in **English**.

## What must be in English

- **Variable names** (e.g. `reminders` not `recordatorios`, `summaryToday` not `resumenHoy`)
- **Function and method names** (e.g. `getSummary` not `getResumen`, `list` not `listar`)
- **Type and interface names** (e.g. `RecordSummary` not `ExpedienteResumen`)
- **File and folder names** (e.g. `recordsService.ts` not `expedientesService.ts`)
- **Comments and JSDoc** (e.g. "Block of recent tasks" not "Bloque de tareas recientes")
- **CSS class names** (e.g. `monthly-activity-card` not `actividad-mensual-card`)
- **Commit messages** and **documentation** in the repo

## User-facing text (i18n)

- **UI labels and messages** shown to the end user may stay in the application's locale (e.g. Spanish for URU).
- Prefer keeping user-facing strings in a dedicated place (e.g. `i18n`, `locales`, or constants) so they can be translated later without touching logic.

